sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as REST Client
    participant Proxy as rest-proxy<br/>8008/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Gateway as gRPC-Gateway<br/>(generated code)
    participant Marshaler as Custom Marshaler<br/>(JSON ↔ Tensor)
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh gRPC<br/>8033/TCP gRPC

    Note over Client,ModelMesh: Flow 1: REST Inference Request

    Client->>Proxy: POST /v2/models/{name}/infer<br/>Content-Type: application/json<br/>Optional TLS
    Proxy->>Gateway: Route to ModelInfer handler
    Gateway->>Marshaler: Parse JSON request body<br/>(nested arrays, base64 BYTES,<br/>multi-dimensional tensors)
    Marshaler->>Marshaler: Flatten arrays → flat tensor contents<br/>Decode base64 BYTES → raw bytes<br/>Map numeric types (BOOL, INT8..FP64)
    Marshaler->>ModelMesh: gRPC ModelInfer RPC<br/>InferRequest protobuf<br/>Optional TLS
    ModelMesh-->>Marshaler: gRPC InferResponse protobuf
    Marshaler-->>Marshaler: Tensor contents → nested JSON arrays<br/>Raw bytes → base64 BYTES<br/>Reshape by output shape
    Marshaler-->>Gateway: JSON response body
    Gateway-->>Proxy: HTTP response
    Proxy-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>application/json

    Note over Client,ModelMesh: Flow 2: Model Metadata Request

    Client->>Proxy: GET /v2/models/{name}<br/>Optional TLS
    Proxy->>Gateway: Route to ModelMetadata handler
    Gateway->>ModelMesh: gRPC ModelMetadata RPC<br/>Optional TLS
    ModelMesh-->>Gateway: ModelMetadataResponse protobuf
    Gateway-->>Proxy: JSON response
    Proxy-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>application/json<br/>(name, versions, platform, inputs, outputs)
